      "updated": 1771570572329,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "routing tiles\nDB\n(TBs of data,\nobj storage)\n- store routing\ntiles",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "center",
      "verticalAlign": "middle",
      "containerId": "zE7TcYnJwUJw29sMcGi68",
      "originalText": "routing tiles DB\n(TBs of data, obj storage)\n- store routing tiles",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "Wdo7_t13zYxpbnfux1xel",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1053.2019095081325,
      "y": 3269.6025036917563,
      "width": 960.8193359375,
      "height": 600,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b4H",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 2131146656,
      "version": 795,
      "versionNonce": 873720416,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1771573698623,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "(1) LOCATION service [QPS]\n- send loc every t secs\n- periodic updates\n- can levarage streams of loc data to improve system\n    - use data to monitor live traffic\n    - detect new roads\n    - analyze user behaviour etc.\n- can levarage location data in near real-time to provide more accurate ETA estimates to the user\n    - reroute if necessary\n\ncontention:\ndo we send every update to server immediately?\n    - no\n    - batch process\n    - buffered on client, sent in batch to the server at lower freq\n    - reduce QPS => but still high in general\n- need DB to handle large write QPS\n- protocol? http with keep-alive option\n\nPOST /v1/locations\n{\n    userId\n    locs (lat, lng, timestamp)\n}",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "(1) LOCATION service [QPS]\n- send loc every t secs\n- periodic updates\n- can levarage streams of loc data to improve system\n    - use data to monitor live traffic\n    - detect new roads\n    - analyze user behaviour etc.\n- can levarage location data in near real-time to provide more accurate ETA estimates to the user\n    - reroute if necessary\n\ncontention:\ndo we send every update to server immediately?\n    - no\n    - batch process\n    - buffered on client, sent in batch to the server at lower freq\n    - reduce QPS => but still high in general\n- need DB to handle large write QPS\n- protocol? http with keep-alive option\n\nPOST /v1/locations\n{\n    userId\n    locs (lat, lng, timestamp)\n}",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "-Y_QKSTVAm4bgZxFwB1oQ",
      "type": "text",
      "x": -705.6816259996449,
      "y": 3094.7692916713177,
      "width": 670.5994873046875,
      "height": 325,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b4I",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 354792352,
      "version": 350,
      "versionNonce": 394399328,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1771573519368,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "(2) Navigation service => CAP + latency\nresponsibel for finding a reasonably fast route from pt A to pt B\n\n- can tolerate a bit of latency\n- route doesnt need to be fastest, but accuracy is critical\n\nGET /v1/nav?origin=1355+market+street,SF&destination=DIsneyland\n-> {\n    distance\n    duration\n    end {lat, lng}\n    ...\n}",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "(2) Navigation service => CAP + latency\nresponsibel for finding a reasonably fast route from pt A to pt B\n\n- can tolerate a bit of latency\n- route doesnt need to be fastest, but accuracy is critical\n\nGET /v1/nav?origin=1355+market+street,SF&destination=DIsneyland\n-> {\n    distance\n    duration\n    end {lat, lng}\n    ...\n}",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "8YxDZQd3mVheHHo_onWjN",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 1797.815693226525,
      "y": 2403.2866515589567,
      "width": 1213.2393798828125,
      "height": 825,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b4J",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1388907424,
      "version": 1967,
      "versionNonce": 1229271648,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1771573682564,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "(3) Map rendering [latency in CPU + Cache && QPS && data usage]\nnote that MEM usage is really high for this in 100sPB\n- not practical to hold entire data set on the client\n- tiles fetched on demand base on client's loc & zoom lvl of client viewport\n\nwhen should the user fetch new map tiles?\n- user is zooming & panning the map viewpoint to explore surroundings\n- during nav, user moves out of the curr map to nearby tile\n\nalot of data is being req-ed & we need a way to serve these tiles\n\nopt1:\nserver builds map tiles on the fly, base on client loc & zoom of view port\nconsidering there is infinite # of loc & zoom level combinations, this is bad\n\n=> puts huge load on server cluster (CPU) to generate ever y map tile dynamically\n=> since the map tiles are dynamically genereated, it is hard to take advantage of caching\n\nopt2:\nserve pre generated set of map tiels at each zoom lvl\n- map tiles are static (IMPT!!)\n- each tile covers a  fixed rectangular grid, using subdivision scheme like geo hashing!\n- there is a uniue geohash associated with each grid\n=> when client needs tile, it first determines the map tile collection to use => based on zoom level [theres only like 20 lvls?]\n=> then copute the map tile URL by converting it slocation tothe geohash (lat, lng) -> (geohash) -> (tile)\n=> these static pre-generated images are served by a CDN\n\nclient makes HTTP req to fetch tile\nCDN can serve same tile to mulitple users => only 1st one has cache miss\n=> approach more scalable as map tiles are served from the nearest POP to the client\n=> static nature makes them highly cacheable\n* without CDN = 300ms\n* with CDN = (<10ms)",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "(3) Map rendering [latency in CPU + Cache && QPS && data usage]\nnote that MEM usage is really high for this in 100sPB\n- not practical to hold entire data set on the client\n- tiles fetched on demand base on client's loc & zoom lvl of client viewport\n\nwhen should the user fetch new map tiles?\n- user is zooming & panning the map viewpoint to explore surroundings\n- during nav, user moves out of the curr map to nearby tile\n\nalot of data is being req-ed & we need a way to serve these tiles\n\nopt1:\nserver builds map tiles on the fly, base on client loc & zoom of view port\nconsidering there is infinite # of loc & zoom level combinations, this is bad\n\n=> puts huge load on server cluster (CPU) to generate ever y map tile dynamically\n=> since the map tiles are dynamically genereated, it is hard to take advantage of caching\n\nopt2:\nserve pre generated set of map tiels at each zoom lvl\n- map tiles are static (IMPT!!)\n- each tile covers a  fixed rectangular grid, using subdivision scheme like geo hashing!\n- there is a uniue geohash associated with each grid\n=> when client needs tile, it first determines the map tile collection to use => based on zoom level [theres only like 20 lvls?]\n=> then copute the map tile URL by converting it slocation tothe geohash (lat, lng) -> (geohash) -> (tile)\n=> these static pre-generated images are served by a CDN\n\nclient makes HTTP req to fetch tile\nCDN can serve same tile to mulitple users => only 1st one has cache miss\n=> approach more scalable as map tiles are served from the nearest POP to the client\n=> static nature makes them highly cacheable\n* without CDN = 300ms\n* with CDN = (<10ms)",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "lnBikKQeG1jLRLnsZrmN0",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 3078.576696358043,
      "y": 2419.7063775090346,
      "width": 810.4195556640625,
      "height": 575,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b4K",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 622574176,
      "version": 668,
      "versionNonce": 1434192480,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1771574399005,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Mobile data usage: [bytes/ min]\n* dont consider client side caching\n- user moves at 30 km/h\n- zoom level where each image covers 200m x 200m (block is 256 * 256 img)\n- ~ 100KB per image\n    * 1 pixel is 1 byte\n    * ~ 100KB\n    - user moves at 30 km/hr\n    - default image covers 200m * 200m\n        - for 1 km * 1 km == 5 * 5 images = 25 images\n        - 25 images * 100 KB = 2.5MB\n    - in an hour, 30 km = 30 * 2.5MB = 75MB per hour\n    - or 1-2MB per min\n\n\nTraffic through CDN:\nmentioned earlier, we serve 5 bil mins of navigation per day\n5 bil * 1.25MB = 6.25 bil MB per day\n== ~62_500MB of data per second\nwith a CDN, these map images are going to be served from POPs all over the world\nassuming 200 POPs\neach POP only needs to serve a few hundred MBs (62,500/200) per second\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Mobile data usage: [bytes/ min]\n* dont consider client side caching\n- user moves at 30 km/h\n- zoom level where each image covers 200m x 200m (block is 256 * 256 img)\n- ~ 100KB per image\n    * 1 pixel is 1 byte\n    * ~ 100KB\n    - user moves at 30 km/hr\n    - default image covers 200m * 200m\n        - for 1 km * 1 km == 5 * 5 images = 25 images\n        - 25 images * 100 KB = 2.5MB\n    - in an hour, 30 km = 30 * 2.5MB = 75MB per hour\n    - or 1-2MB per min\n\n\nTraffic through CDN:\nmentioned earlier, we serve 5 bil mins of navigation per day\n5 bil * 1.25MB = 6.25 bil MB per day\n== ~62_500MB of data per second\nwith a CDN, these map images are going to be served from POPs all over the world\nassuming 200 POPs\neach POP only needs to serve a few hundred MBs (62,500/200) per second\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
    {
      "id": "HMGbAEiEgoo19XpNiEwSP",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 3078.1469956204865,
      "y": 3081.6672943695353,
      "width": 1117.87939453125,
      "height": 500,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 2,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 1,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b4L",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1316464224,
      "version": 924,
      "versionNonce": 1114652256,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": null,
      "updated": 1771574726866,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "Map tiles url:\nhow does the client know whic hURL to fetch from the CDN?\n- opt 2 says map tiles are static, pre-generated\n- 1 unique geo hash per grid, computationally efficient\n- calculation of this lat,lng -> geohash -> URL can be done on client side\n\ni.e. https://cdn.map-provider.com/tiles/9q9hvu.png\n\nkeep in mind,\n- algo to compute is hardcoded in all clients on all different platforms\n- shipping changes to mobile apps in all clients is time-consuming & somewhat risky\n- ensure we want to use this long term => switching to another encoding method takes alog of effort\nOR\n- can consider a service, as an intermediary to contruct the tile URLs based on the same inputs mentioened above\n- simple service\n- added operational flexibility may be worth it\n(to discuss with the interviewer about this)\n\n- when in new zoom lvl / location, map tile service determines which tiles are needed again\n",
      "fontSize": 20,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "Map tiles url:\nhow does the client know whic hURL to fetch from the CDN?\n- opt 2 says map tiles are static, pre-generated\n- 1 unique geo hash per grid, computationally efficient\n- calculation of this lat,lng -> geohash -> URL can be done on client side\n\ni.e. https://cdn.map-provider.com/tiles/9q9hvu.png\n\nkeep in mind,\n- algo to compute is hardcoded in all clients on all different platforms\n- shipping changes to mobile apps in all clients is time-consuming & somewhat risky\n- ensure we want to use this long term => switching to another encoding method takes alog of effort\nOR\n- can consider a service, as an intermediary to contruct the tile URLs based on the same inputs mentioened above\n- simple service\n- added operational flexibility may be worth it\n(to discuss with the interviewer about this)\n\n- when in new zoom lvl / location, map tile service determines which tiles are needed again\n",
      "autoResize": true,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    },
